Exploratory visualizations

Now lets look at some visualizations of our data. Lets look at the relationships between our quantitative variables:

countries %>%
  select(-Country, -Region, -StandardError) %>%
  pairs()

Looks like there are some interesting relationships here. One Im interested in is the relationship between GDPperCapita and LifeExpectancy. Lets see how that varies with region.

ggplot(countries, aes(GDPperCapita, LifeExpectancy,color=Region)) +
  geom_point()

Thats interesting, it looks like the LifeExpectancy in Sub-Saharan Africa is lower than almost all other regions, even when the GDPperCapita is higher. It also looks like the Western European countries all have very high values for both.

Its a bit hard to tell some of these colors apart. Lets look at GDPperCapita separated by region:

ggplot(countries, aes(GDPperCapita, reorder(Region, GDPperCapita),color=Region)) +
  geom_boxplot()
